rComments: Prof. Backman isn't a good prof. She doesn't teach you how to apply content to nursing practice and teaches the bare minimum. She is not helpful if you have legitimate questions and refused to discuss marks with students who were concerned about grades. In fact, she refused to answer any questions at all. Tough grader for no reason (simple course).
I really enjoyed this research seminar. Thank you Dr. Backman for sharing some great insights.
Thank you Prof Backman for all your guidance! You are a very caring person.
Enjoyed the lectures, Prof Backman! Thank you for your availability to answer questions throughout the semester.
Prof Backman is an amazing person. Tough but fair. Cares about patients and students!
Chantal is a good person but not a great prof. Her assignments are not clear, no useful feedback either. She is a tough grader and her lectures are beyond boring
Excellent professor who encourages dialogue and critical thinking
This was one of my favorite professors. This course is heavy, but I do recommend that you do your readings before going to class. I really enjoyed the real case studies.
Prof was great! I really enjoyed the lectures and especially the case studies. If you attend the lectures, you will do well on the exams.
Lecture and textbook material barely cover what is asked in the exam. Be prepared to guess a lot of questions on exams.

Must read the text book and teach yourself. Teacher reads off slides and the content she teaches is not helpful for the exams. She teaches only a small part of the information that is required and does not teach how to apply that information, which is required for the exams.

Lectures are incredibly boring. Be prepared to read the textbook to teach yourself because this prof does not provide and important information in class.
